\v 1 And he called to Moses and the Lord said to him from the tent of meeting saying,
\v 2 “Speak to the children of Israel and you will say to them, ‘A man from you when he brings near an offering to the Lord, from the cattle from the herd and from the sheep you shall bring near your offering.
\v 3 If a burnt offering is an offering from the herd, a perfect male let him offer it to the gate of the tent of meeting let him offer it for favor before the Lord.
\v 4 And he will rest his hand on the head of the burnt offering and it will be accepted\f + \ft Niph., Per., 3ms, hxr\f* for him to make atonement\f + \ft Piel, Inf. Con., rpk\f* for him.
\v 5 And let him slaughter the son of the cattle\f + \ft young bull?\f* before the Lord and let the sons of Aaron the priests bring the blood and let them splash the blood over the altar around where the entrance of the tent of meeting is.
\v 6 And let him skin\f + \ft Hiph., Per., 3ms, fvp\f* the burnt offering and let him cut it up\f + \ft Pi., Perf., 3ms, jtn\f* into its pieces.
\v 7 And let the sons of Aaron the priest put fire on the altar and let them arrange the wood on the fire.
\v 8 And let the sons of Aaron the priests arrange the pieces, the head and the suet, on the wood which is on the fire which is on the altar.
\v 9 And its inward part and its leg bones let him wash with water and let the priest make the sacrifice smoke\f + \ft Hiph., Perf., 3ms, rfq\f* , all of it on the altar as a burnt offering, an offering by fire, a soothing scent to the Lord.
